	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=100779><span id= >golyen</span></a><br><span id=notbold>17 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I wanted to make a few comments related to this thread.<br><br>First, yes, its always the arrow that determines if you are doing magical damage, which is common sense if you think about it .... the arrow is hitting the mob, not the bow.<br><br>Second, I also agree that range should be taken into account as well as ratio, if you can hit a mob farther away, you are more likely to get off multiple shots before it closes to melee.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is not as important if you can snare but its still an issue.<br><br>Third, the price quoted above for shaped darkwood compound bows is too low, IMO.  As a grandmaster fletcher (skill 202), the shaped darkwood compound bow is still insanely hard to make.  Its not unusual to fail multiple times on darkwood, and since the materials to make the bow in question costs around 300pp (a lot depends on CHR and faction), IMO 650pp is unrealistically low for that bow.  800pp seams more reasonable to me.<br><br>Golyen Longbow<br>43 Ranger<br>Grandmaster Fletcher (202)</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
